<Task/><Text-field style="Title" layout="Title"><Font family="Arial">Plotting</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">_________________________________________________________________________________</Text-field><Text-field style="Heading 2" layout="Heading 2">Exercise 1.1</Text-field>
<Group labelreference="L2" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">restart;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group><Text-field style="Text" bold="true" size="14" layout="Normal"><Font size="14" bold="true">(a)</Font></Text-field>
<Group labelreference="L3" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">plot(2*exp(-t)*sin(30*t),t=-1..5);</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output><Text-field style="Maple Plot" layout="Maple Plot"><Plot height="500.0" originalheight="500.0" type="two-dimensional" width="500.0" originalwidth="500.0" plot-scale="1.0" plot-xtrans="0.0" plot-ytrans="0.0" gridlinevisibility="1" legendvisibility="false" input="_ATTRIBUTE(&quot;input&quot; = [TABLE([1 = plot, 2 = [2*exp(-t)*sin(30*t)], 3 = (t = -1 .. 5)]), &quot;originalview&quot; = [-.992499999999999938 .. 4.99249999999999972, -4.85823551937935960 .. 5.39609374478458026]])"></Plot></Text-field>
</Output>
</Group><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">This oscillates and dies away, like the motion of a guitar string after it has been plucked.</Text-field><Text-field style="Text" bold="true" size="14" layout="Normal"><Font size="14" bold="true">(b)</Font></Text-field>
<Group labelreference="L9" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">plot(2*sin(20*t)+3*sin(21*t),t=0..30,numpoints=1000);</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output><Text-field style="Maple Plot" layout="Maple Plot"><Plot height="500.0" originalheight="500.0" type="two-dimensional" width="500.0" originalwidth="500.0" plot-scale="1.0" plot-xtrans="0.0" plot-ytrans="0.0" gridlinevisibility="1" legendvisibility="false" input="_ATTRIBUTE(&quot;input&quot; = [TABLE([1 = plot, 2 = [2*sin(20*t)+3*sin(21*t)], 3 = (t = 0 .. 30), 4 = (numpoints = 1000)]), &quot;originalview&quot; = [0.149999999999999994e-1 .. 29.9849999999999994, -4.93332054431084011 .. 4.95479664485900972]])"></Plot></Text-field>
</Output>
</Group><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">This oscillates rapidly (at the same frequency as <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display=""></Equation>), with the size of the oscillations varying more slowly  (like <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display=""></Equation>).</Text-field><Text-field style="Text" bold="true" size="14" layout="Normal"><Font size="14" bold="true">(c)</Font></Text-field>
<Group labelreference="L15" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">plot(sin(x)+sin(3*x)/3+sin(5*x)/5+sin(7*x)/7,x=0..20);</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output><Text-field style="Maple Plot" layout="Maple Plot"><Plot height="500.0" originalheight="500.0" type="two-dimensional" width="500.0" originalwidth="500.0" plot-scale="1.0" plot-xtrans="0.0" plot-ytrans="0.0" gridlinevisibility="1" legendvisibility="false" input="_ATTRIBUTE(&quot;input&quot; = [TABLE([1 = plot, 2 = [sin(x)+(1/3)*sin(3*x)+(1/5)*sin(5*x)+(1/7)*sin(7*x)], 3 = (x = 0 .. 20)]), &quot;originalview&quot; = [0.250000000000000014e-1 .. 19.9750000000000014, -.930079001700000019 .. .930084151299999995]])"></Plot></Text-field>
</Output>
</Group><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">Half the time this wiggles around near <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display=""></Equation>, and half the time it wiggles around near <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display=""></Equation>.  It jumps quite rapidly between the two levels, and the jumps occur at multiples of <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display="LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYkLUkjbWlHRiQ2JVEjUGlGJy8lJ2l0YWxpY0dRJmZhbHNlRicvJSxtYXRodmFyaWFudEdRJ25vcm1hbEYnRjI=">LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYkLUkjbWlHRiQ2JVEjUGlGJy8lJ2l0YWxpY0dRJmZhbHNlRicvJSxtYXRodmFyaWFudEdRJ25vcm1hbEYnRjI=</Equation> (<Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display=""></Equation> and so on).</Text-field><Text-field style="Text" bold="true" size="14" layout="Normal"><Font size="14" bold="true">(d)</Font></Text-field>
<Group labelreference="L21" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">plot(cos(Pi*x^2),x=-5..5);</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output><Text-field style="Maple Plot" layout="Maple Plot"><Plot height="500.0" originalheight="500.0" type="two-dimensional" width="500.0" originalwidth="500.0" plot-scale="1.0" plot-xtrans="0.0" plot-ytrans="0.0" gridlinevisibility="1" legendvisibility="false" input="_ATTRIBUTE(&quot;input&quot; = [TABLE([1 = plot, 2 = [cos(Pi*x^2)], 3 = (x = -5 .. 5)]), &quot;originalview&quot; = [-4.98749999999999982 .. 4.98749999999999982, -1. .. 1.]])"></Plot></Text-field>
</Output>
</Group><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">The function oscillates between <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display=""></Equation> and <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display="LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYkLUkjbW5HRiQ2JFEiMUYnLyUsbWF0aHZhcmlhbnRHUSdub3JtYWxGJ0Yv">LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYkLUkjbW5HRiQ2JFEiMUYnLyUsbWF0aHZhcmlhbnRHUSdub3JtYWxGJ0Yv</Equation>, with the oscillations becoming more and more rapid as the absolute value of <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display="LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYkLUkjbWlHRiQ2JVEieEYnLyUnaXRhbGljR1EldHJ1ZUYnLyUsbWF0aHZhcmlhbnRHUSdpdGFsaWNGJy9GM1Enbm9ybWFsRic=">LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYkLUkjbWlHRiQ2JVEieEYnLyUnaXRhbGljR1EldHJ1ZUYnLyUsbWF0aHZhcmlhbnRHUSdpdGFsaWNGJy9GM1Enbm9ybWFsRic=</Equation> increases.</Text-field><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">_________________________________________________________________________________</Text-field><Text-field style="Heading 2" layout="Heading 2">Exercise 1.2</Text-field>
<Group labelreference="L27" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">restart;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group hide-input="false" labelreference="L28" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">f := (x) -&gt; (x^3-x)*(x^2-4/9)*(x^2-1/9);</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output><Text-field style="2D Output" layout="Maple Output"><Equation executable="false" style="2D Output" display="">LV9JLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nRzYkJSpwcm90ZWN0ZWRHSShfc3lzbGliRzYiSSxtcHJpbnRzbGFzaEdGKDYkNyM+SSJmR0YoZio2I0kieEdGKEYoNiRJKW9wZXJhdG9yR0YoSSZhcnJvd0dGKEYoKigsJiokOSQiIiQiIiJGNyEiIkY5LCYqJEY3IiIjRjkjISIlIiIqRjlGOSwmRjxGOSNGOkZARjlGOUYoRihGKDcjRi4=</Equation></Text-field>
</Output>
</Group><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">The graph is quite flat and close to zero between <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display=""></Equation> and <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display=""></Equation>, crossing the <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display="LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYkLUkjbWlHRiQ2JVEieEYnLyUnaXRhbGljR1EldHJ1ZUYnLyUsbWF0aHZhcmlhbnRHUSdpdGFsaWNGJy9GM1Enbm9ybWFsRic=">LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYkLUkjbWlHRiQ2JVEieEYnLyUnaXRhbGljR1EldHJ1ZUYnLyUsbWF0aHZhcmlhbnRHUSdpdGFsaWNGJy9GM1Enbm9ybWFsRic=</Equation>-axis seven times, at <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display=""></Equation>  and <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display="LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYkLUkjbW5HRiQ2JFEiMUYnLyUsbWF0aHZhcmlhbnRHUSdub3JtYWxGJ0Yv">LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYkLUkjbW5HRiQ2JFEiMUYnLyUsbWF0aHZhcmlhbnRHUSdub3JtYWxGJ0Yv</Equation>.  The function increases rapidly towards <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display="LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYkLUkjbWlHRiQ2JVEoJiM4NzM0O0YnLyUnaXRhbGljR1EmZmFsc2VGJy8lLG1hdGh2YXJpYW50R1Enbm9ybWFsRidGMg==">LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYkLUkjbWlHRiQ2JVEoJiM4NzM0O0YnLyUnaXRhbGljR1EmZmFsc2VGJy8lLG1hdGh2YXJpYW50R1Enbm9ybWFsRidGMg==</Equation> for <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display=""></Equation>, and drops rapidly towards <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display=""></Equation> for <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display=""></Equation>.  </Text-field>
<Group labelreference="L29" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">plot(f(x),x=-2..2,-0.5..0.5);</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output><Text-field style="Maple Plot" layout="Maple Plot"><Plot height="500.0" originalheight="500.0" type="two-dimensional" width="500.0" originalwidth="500.0" plot-scale="1.0" plot-xtrans="0.0" plot-ytrans="0.0" gridlinevisibility="1" legendvisibility="false" input="_ATTRIBUTE(&quot;input&quot; = [TABLE([1 = plot, 2 = [(x^3-x)*(x^2-4/9)*(x^2-1/9)], 3 = (x = -2 .. 2), 4 = -.5 .. .5]), &quot;originalview&quot; = [-2. .. 2., -82.9629629629629619 .. 82.9629629629629619]])"></Plot></Text-field>
</Output>
</Group><Text-field style="Normal" layout="Normal">The rate of growth is similar to <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display="LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYmLUkjbWlHRiQ2JVEhRicvJSdpdGFsaWNHUSV0cnVlRicvJSxtYXRodmFyaWFudEdRJ2l0YWxpY0YnLUYjNiQtSSVtc3VwR0YkNiUtRiw2JVEieEYnRi9GMi1JI21uR0YkNiRRIjdGJy9GM1Enbm9ybWFsRicvJTFzdXBlcnNjcmlwdHNoaWZ0R1EiMEYnRkFGK0ZB">LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYmLUkjbWlHRiQ2JVEhRicvJSdpdGFsaWNHUSV0cnVlRicvJSxtYXRodmFyaWFudEdRJ2l0YWxpY0YnLUYjNiQtSSVtc3VwR0YkNiUtRiw2JVEieEYnRi9GMi1JI21uR0YkNiRRIjdGJy9GM1Enbm9ybWFsRicvJTFzdXBlcnNjcmlwdHNoaWZ0R1EiMEYnRkFGK0ZB</Equation>, and in fact <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display=""></Equation> is indistinguishable from <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display="LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYmLUkjbWlHRiQ2JVEhRicvJSdpdGFsaWNHUSV0cnVlRicvJSxtYXRodmFyaWFudEdRJ2l0YWxpY0YnLUYjNiQtSSVtc3VwR0YkNiUtRiw2JVEieEYnRi9GMi1JI21uR0YkNiRRIjdGJy9GM1Enbm9ybWFsRicvJTFzdXBlcnNjcmlwdHNoaWZ0R1EiMEYnRkFGK0ZB">LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYmLUkjbWlHRiQ2JVEhRicvJSdpdGFsaWNHUSV0cnVlRicvJSxtYXRodmFyaWFudEdRJ2l0YWxpY0YnLUYjNiQtSSVtc3VwR0YkNiUtRiw2JVEieEYnRi9GMi1JI21uR0YkNiRRIjdGJy9GM1Enbm9ybWFsRicvJTFzdXBlcnNjcmlwdHNoaWZ0R1EiMEYnRkFGK0ZB</Equation> when <Equation executable="false" style="2D Comment" input-equation="" display="LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYkLUkjbWlHRiQ2JVEieEYnLyUnaXRhbGljR1EldHJ1ZUYnLyUsbWF0aHZhcmlhbnRHUSdpdGFsaWNGJy9GM1Enbm9ybWFsRic=">LUklbXJvd0c2Iy9JK21vZHVsZW5hbWVHNiJJLFR5cGVzZXR0aW5nR0koX3N5c2xpYkdGJzYkLUkjbWlHRiQ2JVEieEYnLyUnaXRhbGljR1EldHJ1ZUYnLyUsbWF0aHZhcmlhbnRHUSdpdGFsaWNGJy9GM1Enbm9ybWFsRic=</Equation> is reasonably large.</Text-field>
